WEBVTT

00:00.600 --> 00:06.200
Henry Ford was the leading manufacturer of American automobiles in the early 1900s.

00:09.700 --> 00:12.400
He revolutionized the young automobile industry...

00:12.600 --> 00:15.400
...by developing the assembly line method of production.

00:16.650 --> 00:18.800
By manufacturing his own parts...

00:19.150 --> 00:23.700
...and developing a huge system of conveyors to bring the parts to the assembly line,...

00:24.100 --> 00:27.400
...Ford reduced the cost of manufacturing automobiles.

00:27.700 --> 00:32.900
And Ford passed on much of the savings created by the assembly line production to his customers.

00:34.350 --> 00:38.250
In 1908, when the Ford Motor Company introduced the Model T,...

00:38.600 --> 00:40.850
...it cost $850.

00:41.300 --> 00:48.500
By 1924, assembly line innovations helped reduce the price of a Model T to $290...

00:48.900 --> 00:52.400
...and automobile was now within reach of the average family.

